# @cover src/lib/nogc_sync_mut/simd/scalable.spl 80%
"""
# ScalableVec<T> Unit Tests — Trait Surface (D5 kickoff)

**Feature IDs:** #SIMD-SCALABLE
**Category:** Stdlib
**Difficulty:** 3/5
**Status:** In Progress
**Design:** doc/04_architecture/simd_unified_architecture_detail.md §1.3 §4

## Overview

Unit test for `ScalableVec<T>` splat and runtime lane-count query in
interpreter mode. Corresponds to D5 trait-surface kickoff test ID S-01.

Static method calls on `ScalableVec<f32>` use `::` (deprecated form) because
`ScalableVec<f32>.method()` triggers "expected expression, found Dot" parse
error (parser limitation — `Generic<X>.method()` unsupported in expression
context). See feedback_simd_trait_alias_gap.md.

Current status (D4 partial): S-01 reaches parse-clean execution.
The `lanes()` result depends on D3 interpreter-mode vlenb/svcntw ABI wiring.
Failure (if any) is trait-method-resolution gap, not a spec error.
All tests run in interpreter mode.
"""

use std.spipe.*
use std.simd.{ScalableVec, Vector}


# ============================================================================
# ScalableVec Construction
# ============================================================================

describe "ScalableVec construction":
    """
    ## ScalableVec<T> — D5 trait-surface unit test S-01

    Tests that `ScalableVec<f32>.splat_n(1.0, 4)` constructs successfully in
    interpreter mode with an explicit lane count and that `lanes()` returns
    the given lane count.

    Uses splat_n with explicit n=4 (the architectural minimum for f32 per C2 §4)
    rather than splat() whose runtime vlenb/svcntw ABI may not be wired in
    interpreter mode yet.
    """

    # S-01: ScalableVec<f32>.splat_n(1.0, 4) in interpreter mode
    # lanes() must return the requested lane count (4)
    it "S-01: ScalableVec<f32>.splat_n(1.0 4) constructs and lanes() returns 4":
        val v = ScalableVec<f32>.splat_n(1.0, 4)
        val n = v.lanes()
        expect(n).to_equal(4)
